<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" 
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      metal:use-macro="base"
      i18n:domain="OMCeVmembership">
  <tal:block metal:fill-slot="middle">
    <p class="app-welcome" i18n:translate="app-welcome">
      Why we need your support.
    </p>    
  </tal:block>
  <tal:block metal:fill-slot="middle">
    <h2 i18n:translate="why-headline">Some good reasons.</h2>
  </tal:block>
  <tal:block metal:fill-slot="bottom">
    <h2 i18n:translate="a-new-col-soc">A new Collecting Society</h2>
    <p i18n:translate="history1">
      We have been conducting the Open Music Contest several times, 
      with ever growing interest from the community. Creative Commons Licenses have become a standard. 
    </p>
    <p>
      &nbsp;
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="history2">
      GEMA, the one and only collecting society with regard to music in germany has been a problem and 
      sometimes a real show-stopper. Every time you want to have a CD produced, you need their 
      allowance. Even if the CDs contents were entirely GEMA-free.
    </p>    
    <p>
      &nbsp;
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="reason1">
      GEMA does not support Creative Commons Licenses. The artists registered are not free to 
      release their music the way they want. That's not going to change. 
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="reason2">
      Likewise, artists who do not join GEMA for whatever reasons have no way 
      to get their share of the royalties GEMA collects. 
    </p>
    <p>
      &nbsp;
    </p>
    <p i18n:translate="reason3">
      We are about to set up a new collecting society. 
      We call it C3S: Creative Commons Collecting Society.
      This will be a tremendous effort, so we need your support. Financial and other.
    </p>
    <p>
      &nbsp;
    </p>
    <ul class="links">
      <li>
        <a href="${request.route_url('types')}" i18n:translate="membership-options-link">Membership Options</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="${request.route_url('beitrittserklaerung')}" i18n:translate="join-link">Join</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </tal:block>
</html>
